{"title_page": "1960\u201361 Cincinnati Bearcats men's basketball team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |mode=Basketball\n  |year=1960\u201361\n  |prev_year=1959\u201360\n  |next_year= 1961\u201362\n  |team=Cincinnati Bearcats\n  |image=1961_Cincinnati_Bearcats.jpg\n  |image_size=260px\n  |conference=Missouri Valley Conference \n  |division=\n  |short_conf=MVC\n  |CoachRank=2  \n  |APRank=2  \n  |record=27\u20133\n  |conf_record=10\u20132\n  |head_coach=[[Ed Jucker]]\n  |hc_year=1st\n  |asst_coach1=[[Tay Baker]]\n  |asst_coach2=\n  |asst_coach3=\n  |stadium=Armory Fieldhouse\n  |champion=NCAA champion<br>MVC champion\n  |bowl=[[1961 NCAA University Division Basketball Tournament|NCAA Tournament]]\n  |bowl_result=Champions\n}}\nThe '''1960\u201361 Cincinnati Bearcats men's basketball team''' represented [[University of Cincinnati]]. Cincinnati won the [[1961 NCAA University Division Basketball Tournament|NCAA Tournament]], defeating [[1960\u201361 Ohio State Buckeyes men's basketball team|Ohio State]] 70\u201365 in the Championship Game in [[Kansas City, Missouri]]. The team's head coach was [[Ed Jucker]].\n\n== Roster ==\n{{CBB roster/Header|year=1961|team=Cincinnati Bearcats|teamcolors=y|high_school=yes}}\n\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Bob|last=Wiesenhahn|link=y|num=21|pos=F|ft=6|in=4|lbs=215|class=SR||rs=|home=[[Cincinnati, Ohio]]|high_school=[[Archbishop McNicholas High School|Archbishop McNicholas]]|note=C}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Paul|last=Hogue|link=y|num=22|pos=C|ft=6|in=9|lbs=240|class=JR||rs=|home=[[Knoxville, Tennessee]]|high_school=[[Austin-East High School|Austin]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Tom|last=Thacker|link=y|num=25|pos=G|ft=6|in=2|lbs=170|class=SO||rs=|home=[[Covington, Kentucky]]|high_school=William Grant}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Carl|last=Bouldin|link=y|num=34|pos=G|ft=6|in=2|lbs=180|class=SR||rs=|home=[[Norwood, Ohio]]|high_school=[[Norwood High School (Ohio)|Norwood]