, 1914<br />Eastern Kentucky 34, Western Kentucky 6\n| mostrecent            = September 2, 2017<br />Western Kentucky 31, Eastern Kentucky 17\n| nextmeeting           = September 7, 2024\n| total                 = 85\n| series                = Western Kentucky leads, 47\u201335\u20133\n| largestvictory        = Western Kentucky, 50\u20130 (1930)\n| longeststreak         = Western Kentucky, 13 (1921\u20131941)\n| longestunbeatenstreak = \n| currentstreak         = Western Kentucky, 3 (2007\u20132008, 2017)\n| currentunbeatenstreak = \n| trophy                = None\n| trophy series         = \n| stadiums              =  \n}}\n{{OSM Location map        \n| coord = {{coord|37.2829|-85.3351}}\n| zoom = 7\n| width = 295 \n| height = 250\n| caption = Locations of EKU and WKU\n| mark1 = Red pog.svg\n| label1 = Western Kentucky\n| mark-coord1 = {{coord|36.9854|-86.4561}}\n| label-pos1 = right\n| label-color1 = black\n| mark2 = Brown pog.svg\n| label2 = Eastern Kentucky\n| mark-coord2 = {{coord|37.738|-84.299}}\n| label-pos2 = left\n| label-color2 = black\n}}\n\nThe '''Battle of the Bluegrass''' is the name of the rivalry between the [[Eastern Kentucky Colonels football|Eastern Kentucky Colonels]] and the [[WKU Hilltoppers football|Western Kentucky Hilltoppers]]. Both schools were formerly members of the [[Ohio Valley Conference]], and played against each other regularly until Western Kentucky's transition from the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]]'s [[Football Championship Subdivision|FCS]] to [[Football Bowl Subdivision|FBS]] in 2008. The two teams have met 84 times on the football field, with Western Kentucky currently holding a 47\u201335\u20133 edge in the all-time series.<ref name=\"note1\">{{cite web|date=September 7, 2006 |title=Battle of the Bluegrass to be televised live |publisher=[[The Floyd County Times]] |url=http://www.floydcountytimes.com/view/full_story/1418686/article-Battle-of-the-Bluegrass-to-be-televised-live |accessdate=2013-02-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140607004943/http://www.floydcountytimes.com/view/full_story/1418686/article-Battle-of-the-Bluegrass-to-be-televised-live |archivedate=2014-06-07 }}</ref><ref name=\"note2\">{{cite web |date=September 2, 2008 |title=Hilltoppers Prepare to Face Eastern Kentucky in 85th \"Battle of the Bluegrass\" |publisher=wkusports.com |url=http://www.wkusports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=5400&ATCLID=1573894 |accessdate=2013-02-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080917131133/http://www.wkusports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=5400&ATCLID=1573894 |archivedate=2008-09-17 }}</ref> The series resumed again in 2017, when Western Kentucky hosted Eastern Kentucky in a game played at [[Houchens Industries\u2013L. T. Smith Stadium]].<ref name=\"futuregame\">{{cite web| title=Western Kentucky Hilltoppers Football Schedules and Future Schedules|publisher=fbschedules.com| url=http://www.fbschedules.com/ncaa/conf-usa/western-kentucky-hilltoppers.php|accessdate=2015-01-14}}</ref> The two teams will meet again on September 7, 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fbschedules.com/wku-to-play-at-georgia-in-2026-host-eku-in-2024/|title=WKU to play at Georgia in 2026, host EKU in 2024|last=Kelley|first=Kevin|date=2019-08-12|website=FBSchedules.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref>\n\n==Game results==\n{{Sports rivalry series table\n| cols = 2\n| series_summary = yes\n| format = compact\n| team1 = Eastern Kentucky\n| team1style = {{NCAA color cell|Eastern Kentucky Colonels}}\n| team2 = Western Kentucky\n| team2style = {{NCAA color cell|Western Kentucky Hilltoppers}}\n| 1914 | Richmond, KY | Eastern Kentucky | 34 | Western Kentucky | 6\n| 1914 | Bowling Green, KY | Eastern Kentucky | 0 | Western Kentucky | 18\n| 1915 | Richmond, KY | Eastern Kentucky | 0 | Western Kentucky | 0\n| 1915 | Bowling Green, KY | Eastern Kentucky | 6 | Western Kentucky | 0\n| 1916 | Richmond, KY | Eastern Kentucky | 13 | Western Kentuck